What is TreeMap?

TreeMap stores keys in sorted order.

Internally uses:

Red-Black Tree

Red-Black Tree
Self-balancing Binary Search Tree.

Rules:

Root is black
Red node cannot have red child
Every path has same black nodes
Null nodes are black
Internal Structure
        50(B)
       /    \
    30(R)   70(R)

Each node contains:

key
value
left
right
parent
color
Natural Sorting

Default sorting:

Comparable

Example:

TreeMap<Integer,String> map =
        new TreeMap<>();

Sorted automatically:

1 2 3 4 5
Comparable

Class defines natural ordering.

Example:

class Student implements Comparable<Student> {

    int marks;

    @Override
    public int compareTo(Student s) {
        return this.marks - s.marks;
    }
}
Comparator

External sorting logic.

Example:

TreeMap<Integer,String> map =
    new TreeMap<>(Collections.reverseOrder());

Descending order.

SortedMap

Interface providing:

sorted keys
firstKey()
lastKey()

NavigableMap

Advanced navigation methods.

Important Methods
firstKey()
Smallest key.
map.firstKey();

lastKey()
Largest key.
map.lastKey();

higherKey()
Strictly greater.
map.higherKey(20);

lowerKey()
Strictly smaller.
map.lowerKey(20);

ceilingKey()
Greater OR equal.
map.ceilingKey(20);

floorKey()
Smaller OR equal.
map.floorKey(20);

Example
TreeMap<Integer,String> map =
        new TreeMap<>();

map.put(10,"A");
map.put(20,"B");
map.put(30,"C");

System.out.println(map.higherKey(20));
System.out.println(map.lowerKey(20));
System.out.println(map.ceilingKey(25));
System.out.println(map.floorKey(25));

Output:

30
10
30
20
Tree Balancing

Without balancing:

1
 \
  2
   \
    3

Complexity becomes:

O(n)

Red-Black Tree balances automatically.

Tree Rotations
Left Rotation

Before:

    10
      \
       20
         \
          30

After:

      20
     /  \
   10    30
Right Rotation

Before:

      30
     /
   20
  /
10

After:

      20
     /  \
   10    30
Time Complexity
 | Operation | Complexity |
 | --------- | ---------- |
 | put()     | O(log n)   |
 | get()     | O(log n)   |
 | remove()  | O(log n)   |

TreeMap vs HashMap
| Feature    | TreeMap        | HashMap     |
| ---------- | -------------- | ----------- |
| Ordering   | Sorted         | No order    |
| Structure  | Red-Black Tree | Hash Table  |
| Complexity | O(log n)       | O(1)        |
| Null Key   | No             | One allowed |

